 The chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party Chairman in the Federal Capital Territory, Sunday Zaka, has been reported dead. Zaka was said to have died around 3 am on Saturday after a fatal accident while on his way to his residence in Kuje. READ ALSO: Voters Sleep At Polling Unit With Mosquito Nets Ahead Today’s Election He died alongside his personal security aide after some party activities in the city centre. A chieftain of the party, Michael Kpatuba, who broke the news via a post on his Facebook page on Saturday morning, said, “Dying Election day is really heartbroken to the FCT, PDP family. “Rest in peace, Hon Zaka Sunday, FCT PDP Chairman.”